## Prerequisites

- .NET SDK 8.0 or later
- Appium 2.x
- Android SDK (for Android testing)
- Xcode (for iOS testing on macOS)

## Installation

```bash
# Restore NuGet packages
dotnet restore

# Install Appium globally
npm install -g appium@2

# Install Appium drivers
appium driver install uiautomator2 # For Android
appium driver install xcuitest # For iOS
```

## Configuration

### Environment Variables

Set environment variables or create a launch profile:

```bash
# Platform (Android or iOS)
PLATFORM=Android

# Test environment
TEST_ENV=dev

# Appium server URL
APPIUM_SERVER=http://localhost:4723

# Device configuration
DEVICE_NAME="Android Emulator"
PLATFORM_VERSION=13.0

# App configuration
APP_PATH=/path/to/your/app.apk
APP_PACKAGE=com.example.app
APP_ACTIVITY=.MainActivity

# For iOS
BUNDLE_ID=com.example.app

# Cloud services (optional)
USE_BROWSERSTACK=false
BROWSERSTACK_USERNAME=your_username
BROWSERSTACK_ACCESS_KEY=your_key

USE_SAUCELABS=false
SAUCE_USERNAME=your_username
SAUCE_ACCESS_KEY=your_key

# Timeouts (in seconds)
IMPLICIT_WAIT=10
EXPLICIT_WAIT=30
```

### Test Data

Update test data in:
- `Data/DevData.json` - Development environment
- `Data/QaData.json` - QA environment

### Device Capabilities

Update device capabilities in `Config/CapabilitiesManager.cs` based on your testing needs.

## Running Tests

```bash
# Start Appium server
appium

# Run all tests
dotnet test

# Run tests for specific platform
PLATFORM=Android dotnet test
PLATFORM=iOS dotnet test

# Run with detailed output
dotnet test --logger "console;verbosity=detailed"

# Build in Release mode
dotnet build -c Release

# Clean build artifacts
dotnet clean
```

